[7] Papua New Guinea (Madang)
Date: Tue 9 Sep 2014
Source: ABC Australia Plus [edited]
http://www.radioaustralia.net.au/international/radio/program/pacific-beat/concern-over-deaths-and-rising-measles-cases-in-pngs-madang/1366361


Health authorities in Papua New Guinea's Madang Province are urging people to seek medical assistance immediately if they think they might have measles. At least 10 children in the area have died from the virus already, while there have been more than 1700 confirmed cases. Madang's Director of Health, Marcus Kachau, says the provincial health department is already doing a lot to contain the situation, but he's worried the outbreak will only get worse if it's not managed properly.

